orm, used in examples “I’d have rathered leave before them”, and “I’d have rathered left before them”. %0a%3c The verbal rather has been shown to be most acceptable in the West Coast (California, Nevada, Arizona), and the East Coast, and least acceptable in the South and Midwestern states. %0a%3c %0a%3c Sources:%0a%3c https://ygdp.yale.edu/phenomena/verbal-rather%0a%3c Olaf Koeneman; Marika Lekakou; and Sjef Barbiers. Perfect doubling. Linguistic Variation, 11(1): 35–75. 2011.%0a%3c Rachel Klippenstein. The Behavior-before-Coding Principle in morphosyntactic change: evidence from verbal rather. LSA Annual Meeting Extended Abstracts, 3: 36. April 2012.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
